"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997229","Cabinet Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-11-01T15:51:20.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997229/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997229/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-29","Government Departments: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many contracts the Government holds with cloud based providers to store data; and what the total cost of these contracts to the public purse is.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","185114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997230","Cabinet Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>The original recruitment campaign for the role of Government Chief Security Officer, was unsuccessful. The Cabinet Office is now seeking a 2 year fixed term candidate for this role and this recruitment exercise is underway. Following this, a full recruitment exercise will be undertaken to fill this post permanently.</p><p><strong><em> </em></strong></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-11-01T15:51:57.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997230/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997230/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-29","Government Chief Security Officer: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 6 September 2018 to Question 169860 on Government Chief Security Officer: Public Appointments, when his Department plans to recruit the Government Chief Security Officer.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","185115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997231","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-05","<p>The first selection test for an applicant to either the Regular Naval Service or the Royal Naval Reserve is the Recruitment Test. Subject to the availability of the candidate and a test place, an Armed Forces Careers Office will aim to arrange for the test to take place within 14 days of receipt of an application.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-11-05T17:09:14.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997231/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997231/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Royal Naval Reserve: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average expected period for a person attempting to join the Royal Naval Reserve is from first applying to sitting an entrance assessment.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bowie","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Andrew Bowie","185116"
