"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997372","Home Office","false","2018-11-20","<p>The EU Settlement Scheme provides a streamlined, user-friendly, digital application system, with multiple service options to meet the needs of a varied customer base, including additional support for applicants who may need it.</p><p>In the initial pilot phase (Private Beta 1) applications could be made using a range of ID documents. The second pilot phase, which started on 1 November, aims to test the full digital end-to-end application process, of which the chip checker application is a key component. It allows applicants to prove their identity and the validity of their identity document remotely. We therefore require applicants to use this app when making an application and at this stage they can only do so using a chipped biometric passport.</p><p>Non-EU citizen family members must use a biometric residence card issued by the Home Office in order to prove their identity via the app.</p><p>The second pilot phase will also include some vulnerable individuals being supported by a small number of local authorities and civil society organisations.</p><p>When the Scheme opens more widely, the ID verification app will be only one of three options that applicants can use to verify their identity, along with posting their ID document to us or going to a face-to-face location.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","185059 ; 185060","2018-11-20T13:11:29.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997372/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997372/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997372/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-29","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether chipped identity cards will be accepted as a form of identification in the private beta testing phase of the EU Settlement Scheme.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","185061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997373","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-06","<p>There is no specific definition of a petty offence. As set out in the Answer of 29 October 2018, the Secretary of State was using the phrase petty offender in accordance with its ordinary meaning, namely an offender who commits offences which are not considered serious when compared with some other offences. The seriousness of an offence is determined by two main parameters; the culpability of the offender and the harm caused or risked being caused by the offence.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-11-06T17:31:59.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997373/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997373/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997373/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-29","Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 29 October 2018 to Question 181579 on Offenders, if he will publish offences that are categorised as petty offences.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","184955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997374","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not have any historical debt obligations to Iran and no litigation against the UK Government so no such risk assessments have been made.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","184976 ; 185140","2018-11-01T15:22:19.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997374/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997374/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997374/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Iran: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will conduct a risk assessment of the non settlement of historic debt obligations to Iran; and if he will place a copy of that assessment in the Library.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","185062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997375","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-02","<p>Ministry of Defence officials will consult the organisations who are a party to the protocol and I will write to the hon. Member once that consultation on publication has taken place.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-11-02T14:59:16.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997375/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997375/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Armed Forces: Coroners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 31 October 2016 and follow-up correspondence of 9 January 2017 to Question 49923 on Armed Forces: Coroners, if he will publish the pre- and post-Section 104 Order protocols between the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Defence, the Scottish Government and the Chief Coroner on dealing with military deaths in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","185063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997376","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office provides foreign travel advice for 225 countries and territories to help British nationals living or travelling overseas to make informed decisions about their travel plans. We keep all our travel advice, including for Iran, under constant review to ensure it reflects our current assessment of the risks to British nationals. Our travel advice for Iran makes clear that, currently, British nationals face greater risks in Iran than nationals of many other countries. Any decision to travel to another country is for an individual to take on their own responsibility, after informing themselves of the risks they may face.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-06T14:07:44.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997376/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997376/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997376/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-29","Iran: International Military Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will conduct a risk assessment for (a) UK nationals living in Iran and (b) UK nationals working for UK institutions in Iran of the forthcoming IMS Ltd arbitration hearing.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","185139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997377","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not have any historical debt obligations to Iran and no litigation against the UK Government so no such risk assessments have been made.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","184976 ; 185062","2018-11-01T15:22:19.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997377/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997377/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997377/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Iran: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the merits of continuing the litigation process with Iran on the UK debt to that country.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","185140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997378","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Ministry of Defence operated a total of 183 Sea King helicopters between 1969 and their out of service date in September this year.</p><p>It is not possible to estimate the number of RAF personnel that either crewed or maintained the Sea King helicopter fleet during that period as this information is not held centrally and personnel records do not provide the granularity of detail required.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-06T16:00:23.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997378/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997378/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997378/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Sea King Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) Sea King helicopters purchased by his Department, (b) RAF personal that crewed the Sea King helicopter fleet and (c) RAF service personal, excluding crew members, that were involved in the daily maintenance of the Sea King helicopter fleet between 1969 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","185064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997379","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-06","<p>Sixteen Sea King helicopters were decommissioned in 2016. This included two Sea King HU Mk 5 helicopters which were retired from Ministry of Defence service and placed in the disposal reserve, until being regenerated for lease to a company, HeliOperations Ltd, for training purposes. This lease ended in September 2018.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-06T15:58:02.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997379/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997379/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997379/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Sea King Helicopters: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Sea King helicopters were decommissioned in 2016; and if any of those helicopters were subsequently brought back into service.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","185065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997380","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-06","<p>Yes, standard maintenance of the Sea King helicopter included maintenance of the engine, gearbox and the heating and ventilation system.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-06T15:58:52.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997380/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997380/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997380/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Sea King Helicopters: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the standard maintenance cycle of the Sea King helicopter included maintenance of the (a) engine, (b) gearbox and (c) heating and ventilation system.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","185066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997381","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) has known about the presence of asbestos in Sea King helicopters since they entered service in 1969 and it has been managed in accordance with the regulations in place at the time.</p><p>As part of the wider remit to reduce and eliminate Asbestos Containing Materials (ACM) in military systems, progressive action was taken since 1999 to reduce ACM in the Sea King fleet. By 2006, as major ACM components had been replaced and the risk was identified as very low, remaining ACM components were replaced as and when maintenance allowed.</p><p>Earlier this year, a routine maintenance training activity being conducted on a retired Sea King airframe revealed the presence of asbestos and immediate containment measures were put in place. Subsequent investigation identified that the MOD supply chain had not been purged of ACM components, with the risk that these components could still be fitted to Sea King helicopters. Action has been taken to remove these components from the supply chain, initial guidance has been issued to serving and former personnel and further information will be made available as soon as we are able to do so.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-06T15:59:36.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997381/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997381/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Sea King Helicopters: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department was first notified of asbestos in the Sea King helicopter fleet.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","185067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997382","Home Office","false","2018-11-20","<p>It is longstanding policy not to disclose details of records which may be held in relation to individuals’ arrival in the United Kingdom, as to do so would not be in the interests of national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-11-20T17:44:27.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997382/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997382/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-29","International Military Services: Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether members of the Iranian delegation attending the IMS Ltd. arbitration court hearing with the UK have been detained by the UK authorities since their previous detention upon entry in 2013.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","185141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997383","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-01","<p>The dispute is the subject of ongoing litigation initiated by the Ministry of Defence and Support for the Armed Forces of Iran against International Military Services Ltd. It would not be appropriate for the Government to comment.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-01T15:28:33.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997383/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997383/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997383/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-29","Iran: International Military Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reason the Chieftain tank debt dispute with Iran has not been settled; and what the main impediments are which prevent the resolution of that issue by IMS Ltd.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","185142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997384","Attorney General","false","2018-11-05","<p>As of 30 September 2018 the Serious Fraud Office employed:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Permanent Staff</p></td><td><p>400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fixed term contract</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Agency</p></td><td><p>126</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Secondment or loan</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-11-05T14:27:39.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997384/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997384/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997384/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-10-29","Serious Fraud Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many staff (a) employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Serious Fraud Office.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997385","Cabinet Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Civil Service Commission currently employs 19 members of staff (18.2 Full Time Equivalent). The secretariat is staffed entirely by civil servants on loan/secondment from a range of government departments, and new recruits are employed by the Cabinet Office prior to being seconded to the Commission.</p><p> </p><p>The Commission also provides secretariat services for the Office of the Commissioner for Public Appointments (OCPA) and the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments (ACOBA) from within these staff numbers.</p><p> </p><p>The Commission publishes this information, as at 31 March, each year as part of its Annual Report and Accounts, which can be viewed on the Commission’s website, Gov.uk and is available in the libraries in the Houses of Parliament.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-11-01T15:48:55.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997385/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997385/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997385/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-29","Civil Service Commission: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Civil Service Commission.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997386","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-02","<p>HM Land Registry employs (a) 5293 members of staff directly, (b) 1 member of staff on secondment, and (c) 22 members of staff under contract.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-11-02T14:37:50.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997386/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997386/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-29","Land Registry: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many staff (a) are employed directly by (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in HM Land Registry.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997387","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-11-06","<p>The National Archives (a) employ 499 staff directly. They have no staff seconded or loaned into the Department and no contractors.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-11-06T17:00:13.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997387/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997387/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-29","National Archives: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the National Archives.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997388","Department for Education","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Children’s Commissioner’s Office consists of 29 employed members of staff. 28 members of staff are directly employed members of staff, including the Children’s Commissioner. This is equivalent to 27.2 full time posts. One member of staff is currently seconded from a government department.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-11-06T14:14:36.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997388/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997388/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-29","Children's Commissioner for England: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Office of the Children's Commissioner.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997389","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-11-01","<p>At the end of September 2018 the Westminster Government funded part of the Forestry Commission which includes Forestry Commission England/Central Services, Forest Enterprise England and Forest Research. Collectively, these organisations employ the following staff:</p><p> </p><p>(a) Directly employed: 1,525 (1,420 full time equivalent)</p><p>(b) Seconded: 1 (0.5 full time equivalent)</p><p>(c) Under contract: 121 (93 full time equivalent)</p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-11-01T14:22:52.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997389/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997389/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-10-29","Forestry Commission: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many staff (a) are employed directly by (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Forestry Commission.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997390","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>The table below outlines the response from Civil Aviation Authority (CAA):</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Number of staff directly employed by the CAA as at 28<sup>th</sup> September 2018</strong></p></td><td><p>1270</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Number of staff seconded to the CAA as at 19<sup>th</sup> October 2018</strong></p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Number of staff working under contract in the CAA as at 30<sup>th</sup> October 2018</strong></p></td><td><p>65</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Please note that this data has been provided for varying dates. This is due to the data being held on a number of systems and the date on which the data was extracted.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-11-06T16:34:11.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997390/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997390/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-29","Civil Aviation Authority: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Civil Aviation Authority.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997391","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-05","<p>The number of staff directly employed at the Pensions Regulator as of the 30 September is 685; 9 staff are under contract.</p><p> </p><p>The figure for those seconded is below 5.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on The Pensions Regulator headcount can be found in their Annual Report and Accounts, which can be found via the following Link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/docs/annual-report-and-account-2017-2018" target="_blank">http://www.thepensionsregulator.gov.uk/docs/annual-report-and-account-2017-2018</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-11-05T15:28:20.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997391/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997391/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-29","Pensions Regulator: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many staff are (a) employed directly by (b) seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Pensions Regulator.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997392","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-06","<p>The number of staff within Public Health England (PHE), reported as both number of separate individual persons (headcount) and Whole Time Equivalents (WTE) as at 30 September 2018 are available in the following table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Headcount</p></td><td><p>WTE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Employed directly by PHE</p></td><td><p>5,395</p></td><td><p>5,004</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Seconded to PHE</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>11.73</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Work under contract in PHE*</p></td><td><p>63</p></td><td><p>61.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>*‘PHE has interpreted “work under contract” as “contingent labour”.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-11-06T15:22:49.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997392/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997392/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-29","Public Health England: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care,  how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in Public Health England.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997393","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>(a) Employed directly -10750</p><p>(b) Secondees - 0</p><p>(c) Work under contract*- 1115</p><p>Total 11865</p><p> </p><p><strong>* </strong>This figure is a total of external Non-Permanent Workers (NPW) that the British Council have recorded both in the UK and overseas, this however does not capture invigilators/examiners, those provided by other companies to fulfil contracts or other cases of short term duration external workers.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-01T16:06:23.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997393/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997393/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-29","British Council: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many staff (a) are employed directly by, (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the British Council.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997394","Treasury","false","2018-11-01","<p>As at the 30th September 2018 the Office of Budget Responsibility employed 30.08 FTE (Full time Equivalent) Staff. There were no staff seconded to the department or working under contract.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-11-01T14:30:51.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997394/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997394/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-10-29","Office for Budget Responsibility: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer,  how many staff (a) are employed directly by (b) are seconded to and (c) work under contract in the Office for Budget Responsibility.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","185153"
